{
  "stem": "1141.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] And the life there was quite miserable, because people who couldn't work anymore, they were being beaten up or shoot.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were collapsing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so when we left Oberschlesien--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were little towns around-- surrounded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was on the Polish-German border.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we realized that there was something going on because of the shooting and the planes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we were even afraid to look up into the sky, because we were watched.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, we were afraid for our own shadow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By that time, we were not human anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "By that time, we couldn't think.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We couldn't apprehend the situation, because we were like zombies-- they would call it in this country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe that, now that my daughter is a doctor, and I read a lot about how they managed to brainwash people and how they managed to numb somebody's mind, or cripple your mind-- in Auschwitz, in the food, they put in bromide.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This friend of mine who worked in the kitchen said that every barrel of soup, they used to put in five kilograms of bromide-- which prevents people from-- it's like a tranquilizer.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It stopped women from menstruating.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It-- your mind gets numb.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm not a doctor, but from what I-- I hear and read and understand that, they used some kind of a method to just take away your human-- that you're a human being.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She's here.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She's here.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She had-- she had two children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She's a-- she is a schoolteacher here.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she's extremely-- she's suffering from malignant-- malignant cancer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- I would like you to interview her if possible, if she's able to.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her name is Ms.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Adler-- Beszy Adler.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was more-- she was already an older-- older girl.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
